CHANGELOG.md:111:- Added depth-2 sampler-dispatch planning helpers (frac-0023): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/sampler_dispatch.py` now exposes a frozen `SamplerDispatchPlan` plus `grain_density_band`, `sampler_synth_arg_pairs`, `build_s_new_args`, `build_sampler_dispatch_plan`, and `summarize_sampler_dispatch_plan` so diagnostics and composer callers can inspect a concrete `sw_sampler` dispatch before or after buffer loading. The plan reports sample path, mode, key, buffer state, density band, key-derived or explicit transposition, gain-db-adjusted effective amp, FX preset pairs, and the canonical `/s_new` synth argument pairs; live `SamplerDispatcher.dispatch_sample` now uses the same `build_s_new_args` helper, preserving existing OSC ordering and lifecycle behavior. `tests/test_sampler_dispatch_depth.py` pins named density bands, loaded/unloaded plan output, JSON-safe summaries, end-to-end plan-to-dispatch matching, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_sampler_dispatch.py` and the startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:113:- Added depth-2 sample-lab report helpers (frac-0022): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/sample_lab.py` now exposes a frozen `SamplePlanReport` dataclass plus pure helpers `density_band`, `threshold_band`, `intensity_band`, `build_sample_plan_report`, and `summarize_sample_plan_report` so EMSD operator/diagnostics callers can resolve a `SamplePlan` together with its `sample_bank` freshness and fallback rule into one operator-readable view (source identity and capture path, refresh and freshness seconds, fallback list, cadence state, section function, transforms tuple plus count, density and named density band, buffer seconds, trigger threshold and named threshold band, intensity and named intensity band, and study focus) and emit a stable JSON-safe summary. Existing `SAMPLE_SOURCES`, `SAMPLE_SOURCE_ALIASES`, `SAMPLE_FALLBACKS`, `canonical_sample_source_name`, `sample_source`, `sample_bank`, and `plan_environmental_sampling` semantics are preserved (cadence and section-function shaping unchanged); `SamplePlan` now also carries the resolved `cadence_state` so reports can be built without re-passing it. `tests/test_sample_lab_depth.py` pins the band cutpoints, plan/bank field mirroring, alias-to-canonical bank resolution, section-function carry-through, JSON-safe summary shape, end-to-end downstream use, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_sample_lab.py`, `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence`, and `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` remain regression anchors.
