CHANGELOG.md:123:- Added depth-2 metric accent report helpers (frac-0017): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/render/rules/metric_accent.py` now exposes frozen `LaneMetricAccentStat` and `MetricAccentReport` dataclasses plus `lane_metric_accent_stat`, `analyze_metric_accent`, and `summarize_metric_accent_report` so diagnostics can apply the R1 rule once and inspect per-lane shaping outcomes (lane name, role, meter, step count, shaped-step count, mean multiplier, strongest row, and applies flag), aggregate totals across `TrackerScene`, `TrackerSong`, or `TrackerPattern` inputs with a stable `score_kind`, and emit a JSON-safe operator summary. Existing `METRIC_ACCENT_4_4`, `metric_accent_table`, `MetricAccentRule.apply`, and `apply_metric_accent` semantics are preserved; `tests/test_metric_accent_depth.py` pins the new report surface and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_metric_accent_rule.py`, `tests/test_role_gate_integration.py`, and startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
