CHANGELOG.md:131:- Added depth-2 phrase tracker helpers (frac-0013): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/phrase_tracker.py` now exposes frozen `PhraseBoundary` / `PhraseStreamSummary` dataclasses plus `track_phrase_boundaries`, `summarize_phrase_stream`, and `phrase_status_snapshot` so listener tick streams can produce stable typed boundary records, completed-phrase counts, total/longest durations, and listener-shaped status snapshots while preserving the existing `PhraseTracker.update()` event contract used by MIDI, Theramini, and phrase capture runtime paths. `tests/test_phrase_tracker_depth.py` pins the new stream helpers and fractal depth, while existing tracker, capture, listener, and startup identity anchor tests remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:133:- Added depth-2 genre literacy helpers (frac-0012): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/genre_literacy.py` now exposes frozen `GenreSummary` / `GenreBlend` dataclasses plus pure helpers `summarize_strategy`, `genre_compatibility`, `blend_genre_strategies`, and `recommend_genre_sequence` so cast-planner, mix, and operator-diagnostics callers can render a stable per-genre summary (label, tempo range, texture density, chromatic tolerance, voice count, dominant grooves, top arc phases, calm/balanced/intense mood bucket), score a bounded `[0.0, 1.0]` symmetric compatibility between two traditions from arc-affinity cosine, modal/groove Jaccard ratios, and texture/chromatic distance, blend numeric hints with a clamped `[0.0, 1.0]` weight (tempo range, texture density, chromatic tolerance, rubato tolerance, repetition tolerance, spatial width, sorted shared modal preferences), and plan one genre per supplied arc phase with rolling fatigue from prior selections. Existing `GenreStrategy`/`REQUIRED_GENRES` data, `strategy_for_genre`, `all_strategies`, `genre_arc_affinity`, `best_genres_for_phase`, and `select_genre` semantics are preserved; `tests/test_genre_literacy_depth.py` pins summary stability and mood bucketing, compatibility self-identity / symmetry / boundedness with related-vs-contrasted ranking, blend interpolation / clamp / modal intersection, sequence per-phase coverage with no immediate repeats, while `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence` and `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` remain regression anchors.
