my-claw/sdp/prd-gallery-display.md:5:Turn the CypherClaw server's physical monitor into a living art gallery. The attached 1280x1024 display (Intel UHD 630, `/dev/fb0`) auto-launches a gallery on boot that showcases GlyphWeave art — both ANSI terminal art on tty1 and full-color framebuffer pixel renders. New pieces from the Art Studio appear automatically as they're created. Rich keyboard controls let Anthony browse, filter, favorite, and trigger new art. An ambient info overlay (togglable) shows pet status, server health, pipeline progress, and piece attribution.
