                singleton so importing the package never touches the\n                             filesystem (clean test ergonomics).\n      - __main__.py          uvicorn entry: `python -m cypherclaw.image_api`\n      - config.py            env-var Settings dataclass with from_env classmethod\n    \n    Systemd unit: my-claw/systemd/cypherclaw-image-api.service\n      - User=user, EnvironmentFile=/home/user/cypherclaw/.env (AWS keys)\n      - Restart=always with backoff; hardened (NoNewPrivileges, ProtectSystem,\n        ReadWritePaths=/home/user/cypherclaw-data only)\n      - Default port 9000, host 0.0.0.0 (tailnet-bound only at deploy)\n    \n    Tests (51 new, all passing locally; 3264 total still green):\n      - test_image_api_spec_parser   Shape A + B + project-slug coherence + errors\n      - test_image_api_jobs_db       insert/get/update lifecycle, list_pending,\n                                     persistence across reopen, parent-dir create\n      - test_image_api_s3_uploader   FakeS3Client; URL format, put_object args,\n                                     alt region/prefix, default content-type\n      - test_image_api_worker        full lifecycle with mocked Gemini + S3,\n                                     Gemini refusal → failed, upload fail → failed,\n                                     idempotent on terminal jobs, ordering checks\n      - test_image_api_app           FastAPI TestClient end-to-end: 202 + job_id,\n                                     polling to completed, Shape B accepted,\n                                     400 on no-prompt, 404 on unknown id,\n                                     failure path surfaces error in poll\n    \n    Tasks #21 (package), #22 (TDD suite), #23 (systemd unit) complete.\n    Tasks #20 (AWS bucket+IAM) and #24 (deploy + smoke test) still pending —\n    #20 needs admin AWS creds, #24 needs #20 to land first.\n\nsrc/cypherclaw/image_api/__main__.py"}
