nd 5xx retry with exponential backoff bounded to 3 attempts, honoring `Retry-After`. (~3h)\n-- **T-003** [T2] Implement `ModalClient` parallel implementation of `GenerationClient` Protocol. (~6h)\n-- **T-004** [T2] Provide `LocalAdaClient` stub raising `NotImplementedError`. (~6h)\n-- **T-005** [T2] Implement live smoke test against real Replicate that asserts a 30 s WAV is produced and cost is recorded. (~6h)\n-- **T-006** [T1] Implement `GenerationStorage.save(result, request)` writing WAV to `samples/generated/<yyyy-mm-dd>/<hash>.wav` and registering `SampleRecord`. (~3h)\n-- **T-007** [T1] Extend `SampleLibrary` to accept `source=\"generated\"`. (~3h)\n-- **T-008** [T1] Implement `GenerationQueue` SQLite-backed persistent queue with idempotent enqueue. (~3h)\n-- **T-009** [T1] Implement async worker loop `GenerationQueue.run_worker()` that processes pending items end-to-end. (~3h)\n-- **T-010** [T1] Implement bounded retry on transient generation failures with `attempts` column. (~3h)\n+- **T-001** [T2] `POST /memory/search` — wraps `NarrativeMemory` semantic search; accepts `{query, k, domain_filter}`, returns ranked results (~6h)\n+- **T-002** [T1] `GET /events?since_event_id=…&domain=…` — paginated event log read; supports incremental tail-reading from a known event ID (~3h)\n+- **T-003** [T2] `POST /events` — append a narrative event to the world state event log; used by Deniable to record raid outcomes that should propagate via shared narrative state (~6h)\n+- **T-004** [T1] systemd user service `cypherclaw-narrative-api.service` enabled and started; survives reboot; logs to journal (~3h)\n+- **T-005** [T2] Pytest test suite covering each endpoint with at least: success path, auth failure (when enabled), bad input validation, downstream-engine error handling (~6h)\n+- **T-006** [T1] Update PromptClaw `ESCALATIONS.md` with operator action items: enable systemd user-service lingering (`loginctl enable-linger user`) so the service runs without an active SSH session; configure `NARRATIVE_AUTH_TOKEN` if defense-in-depth desired; document Deniable Mac's Tailscale IP in firewall allowlist (if any) (~3h)\n \n-*Subtotal: ~39 hours*\n-\n-### Sprint 2: Quality Scoring\n-\n-**Depends on:** Sprint 0 (Versioning System), Sprint 1 (Quality Scoring)\n-\n-- **T-011** [T2] Write operator runbook at `docs/runbooks/generation-backend.md`. (~6h) → deps: T-001\n-- **T-012** [T1] End-to-end smoke test on cypherclaw producing one real generated sample audible in a piece. (~3h) → deps: T-001\n-\n-*Subtotal: ~9 hours*\n-\n-### Sprint 3: Improvement Engine Hardening\n-\n-**Depends on:** Sprint 0 (Versioning System), Sprint 2 (Improvement Engine Hardening)\n-\n-- **T-013** [T1] Implement `_post_song_generation_hook(score, learning, mood, mode, clap_centroid)` in `tools/duet_composer.py`. (~3h) → deps: T-011\n-- **T-014** [T1] Implement `_should_queue_now(mode, mood, learning)` heuristic based on cycle rate and homogeneity flags. (~3h) → deps: T-011\n-- **T-015** [T1] Add systemd unit `cypherclaw-generation-worker.service` running the queue worker. (~3h) → deps: T-011\n-- **T-016** [T1] Implement `tools/generation_worker.py` as the standalone async worker entry point. (~3h) → deps: T-011\n-- **T-017** [T1] Implement `/tmp/generation_status.json` diagnostic file written every 30 s by the worker. (~3h) → deps: T-011\n-- **T-018** [T2] Wire generation status into `operator_diagnostics.py` so the face/inkplate display can show \"♫ generating\" / \"♫ queued: N\". (~6h) → deps: T-011\n-- **T-019** [T1] Extend `usage_journal.jsonl` to tag each played sample by source. (~3h) → deps: T-011\n-- **T-020** [T1] Add `generated_content_dominance` antipattern detector to `render/antipatterns.py`. (~3h) → deps: T-011\n-- **T-021** [T1] Implement self-distance prior on `GenerationConditioner` rejecting requests too similar to recent generations. (~3h) → deps: T-011\n-\n-*Subtotal: ~30 hours*\n+*Subtotal: ~27 hours*\n \n ### Sprint 5: Library & CRUD Polish\n \n-**Depends on:** Sprint 0 (Versioning System), Sprint 1 (Quality Scoring)\n+**Depends on:** Sprint 0 (Versioning System), Sprint 1 (Library & CRUD Polish)\n \n-- **T-022** [T1] Define `GenerationRequest` frozen dataclass with prompt, clap_centroid (np.ndarray[512]), duration_sec, seed, backend, model, bpm_target, mode_name, arc_phase fields. (~3h) → deps: T-001\n-- **T-023** [T1] Implement `GenerationRequest.hash()` content-addressed identity that excludes `backend` and includes prompt, clap_centroid bytes, duration, seed, model, bpm_target. (~3h) → deps: T-001\n-- **T-024** [T1] Implement `GenerationConditioner.build_request(mode, arc_phase, mood, clap_centroid, duration_sec)` returning `GenerationRequest` with deterministic prompt and seed. (~3h) → deps: T-001\n-- **T-025** [T1] Define per-mode prompt fragment table for solitary, companion, working_ambience, evening_reflection, storm. (~3h) → deps: T-001\n-- **T-026** [T1] Define per-arc-phase fragment overlays (Emergence, Crystallization, Divination, Convergence, Conversation, Reflection, etc.) feeding into prompt composition. (~3h) → deps: T-001\n-- **T-027** [T1] Implement `GenerationBudget` with daily and monthly USD caps, atomic persistence, and date-rollover. (~3h) → deps: T-001\n-- **T-028** [T1] Implement `GenerationCache` content-addressed audio cache with LRU + size-cap eviction. (~3h) → deps: T-001\n-- **T-029** [T1] Implement `validate_audio(path)` rejecting silent / clipped / NaN / wrong-format files. (~3h) → deps: T-001\n-- **T-030** [T1] Define `GenerationClient` Protocol and `GenerationResult` dataclass. (~3h) → deps: T-001\n+- **T-007** [T1] Domain-column migration: additive `ALTER TABLE entities ADD COLUMN domain TEXT DEFAULT 'shared'` and same on `events` table per `deniable_narrative_integration_v1.md` §3; non-breaking, existing rows default to 'shared'; runs as a `narrative/migrations/` Alembic step or equivalent (~3h) → deps: T-001\n+- **T-008** [T1] FastAPI scaffold at `~/cypherclaw/src/cypherclaw/narrative_api/` with Pydantic settings (binding address, port, auth token from .env), uvicorn entry point, structured logging via structlog (~3h) → deps: T-001\n+- **T-009** [T1] `GET /health` endpoint returning JSON `{status, narrative_engine_importable, world_db_reachable, ollama_reachable, version, uptime_seconds}` (~3h) → deps: T-001\n+- **T-010** [T1] Shared-secret auth: optional `X-Narrative-Auth` header validated against env-var token; if `NARRATIVE_AUTH_TOKEN` is unset, auth is disabled (warning logged); if set, mismatched/missing token returns 401 (~3h) → deps: T-001\n+- **T-011** [T2] `POST /beats/next` — wraps `NarrativeEngine.next_beat()` per integration spec §6; accepts `{cycle_number, domain_filter, arc_position_target?, force_arc_event?}`, returns serialized `StoryBeat` JSON (~6h) → deps: T-001\n+- **T-012** [T1] `GET /world/entities?domain=…&type=…` — returns entities filtered by domain (defaults to 'shared') and optional type; pagination via `limit + offset` (~3h) → deps: T-001\n+- **T-013** [T1] `GET /world/entities/{entity_id}` — returns single entity with full properties JSON; 404 if not found (~3h) → deps: T-001\n+- **T-014** [T2] `POST /world/entities` — create new entity with `{type, name, domain, properties}`; validates domain in `{shared, cypherclaw, deniable}`; returns created entity with assigned ID (~6h) → deps: T-001\n+- **T-015** [T2] `PATCH /world/entities/{entity_id}` — apply state mutations to entity per integration spec `StateMutation` shape (set/increment/decrement/append/remove on field path); returns updated entity (~6h) → deps: T-001\n \n-*Subtotal: ~27 hours*\n+*Subtotal: ~36 hours*\n \n ### Sprint 6: Stretch Goals\n \n **Depends on:** Sprint 0 (Versioning System)\n \n-- **T-031** [T2] Implement weekly KL-divergence audit between current IDyOM LTM and a frozen week-0 snapshot. (~6h)\n-- **T-032** [T2] Document the cost model and verify steady-state stays under cap for ≥7 consecutive days. (~6h)\n+- **T-016** [T1] Smoke test from Deniable: a small CLI script (`scripts/smoke_narrative.py` in the cypherclaw repo) that calls each endpoint and confirms reachability; documented in README so the Deniable operator can validate from the Mac after Tailscale connection (~3h)\n \n-*Subtotal: ~12 hours*\n+*Subtotal: ~3 hours*\n \n ---\n \n ## Requirements Coverage\n \n-- **MUST requirements:** 30/30 covered\n-- **SHOULD requirements:** 2 included as stretch\n+- **MUST requirements:** 15/15 covered\n+- **SHOULD requirements:** 1 included as stretch\n \n **✓ All MUST requirements covered.**\n \ndiff --git a/sdp/logs/Lead_T-014_20260427T001208Z_1777312399.log b/sdp/logs/Lead_T-014_20260427T001208Z_1777312399.log\nindex bd315b2..3d24595 100644\n--- a/sdp/logs/Lead_T-014_20260427T001208Z_1777312399.log\n+++ b/sdp/logs/Lead_T-014_20260427T001208Z_1777312399.log\n@@ -2,3 +2,6 @@ Command: env -u CLAUDECODE claude --dangerously-skip-permissions --model claude-\n Prompt delivered via: stdin (762 chars)\n ---\n \n+Working tree clean.\n+\n+T-014's `_should_queue_now` heuristic was already implemented in commit `b854f62` (covering all four acceptance branches: cold start, 30-min rate gate via `learning[\"last_generation_enqueued_at\"]`, sampler-dominating antipattern, $0.50 budget floor, and `working_ambience` + `arc_payoff < 0.4`), with 10 passing tests in `tests/test_generation_composer_hook.py`. The previous attempt's leftover SDP runtime artifacts are now committed in two `chore(sdp): flush ...` commits following the existing convention.\ndiff --git a/sdp/logs/Verify_T-014_20260427T001208Z_1777312500.log b/sdp/logs/Verify_T-014_20260427T001208Z_1777312500.log\nindex e73c7d1..111a7e0 100644\n--- a/sdp/logs/Verify_T-014_20260427T001208Z_1777312500.log\n+++ b/sdp/logs/Verify_T-014_20260427T001208Z_1777312500.log\n@@ -219,3 +219,19 @@ Prompt delivered via: argv\n {\"type\":\"message\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-27T17:56:55.178Z\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"I will now stage the verification log\",\"delta